# Chief Medical Officer SOP

  [bold]1.[/bold] The Chief Medical Officer is permitted to carry a regular Defibrillator or a Compact Defibrillator on their person at all times;

  [bold]2.[/bold] The Chief Medical Officer is permitted to carry a flash and their hypospray;

  [bold]3.[/bold] The Chief Medical Officer is permitted to carry self-defense chemicals for their hypospray if the station alert level warrants it;

  [bold]4.[/bold] The Chief Medical Officer is not permitted to allow the creation of poisonous or explosive mixtures in Chemistry without express consent from the [color=#cb0000]Head of Security[/color] or, failing that, the presence of a clear and urgent danger to the integrity of the station;

  [bold]5.[/bold] The Chief Medical Officer must make sure that any reviveable corpses are revived.
